🔹 6️⃣ Request Context (🔥 real data):-
👉 Request Context = wo data jo batata hai ki request kis liye, kis pe, kisne aur kaise ki hai.
-------------------------------------------------------------
6(1)Target Identity = wo user (identity) jiske upar change apply hoga

6.2️⃣ Requested By (kisne request kiya)
👉 Request kisne initiate ki
Requested By: manager1 / self / admin

6.3️⃣ Request Type
👉 Kis type ka request hai
ACCESS_REQUEST
ROLE_REQUEST
ACCOUNT_REQUEST
PASSWORD_RESET

6.4️⃣ Target Object / Resource
👉 Kis object pe action ho raha hai
Role: IT Admin
Application: Salesforce
Entitlement: Read Access

6.5️⃣ Action Details
👉 Kya change hona hai
ADD
REMOVE
UPDATE
ENABLE
DISABLE

6.6️⃣ Application / System Context
👉 Kis system me change ho raha hai
Application: SAP / Salesforce / AD

6.7️⃣ Business Justification (🔥 important)
👉 Kyun request kiya gaya
"User ko project ke liye access chahiye"
👉 Audit me bahut important hota hai

6.8️⃣ Priority / Urgency
👉 Kitna urgent hai
LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH

6.9️⃣ Time / Schedule Info
👉 Kab apply hoga
Immediate
Scheduled (future date)

6.🔟 Additional Attributes (Custom data):
👉 Extra info jo developer add kare
projectName: "BankingApp"
location: "India"
--------------------------------------------------------
()Purpose / Kaam:-

()Execution Environment:-
Ye batata hai ki request kaunse point par hai, kaunsa work item execute ho raha hai,
aur workflow case me request ka status kya hai.

()Attributes & Parameters:-
Request ke key-value attributes aur approval items hold karta hai.

()Workflow Integration:-
WorkflowCase aur WorkItem ko track karta hai, taaki system samajh sake ki kaun sa step complete hua, kaun sa pending hai.

()Comments & Notifications:-
Approver ke comments aur notification templates manage karta hai.

()Validation & Approval:-
Runtime me request ke validation rules aur approval mode check karne me use hota hai.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()Kya RequestContext DB me store hota hai?
Answer:-
Nahi, RequestContext khud DB me directly store nahi hota.
Ye ek runtime object hai jo request ke execution ke dauran memory me exist karta hai.

()Detail Explanation:-
Runtime vs Persistent Data
RequestContext sirf workflow execution ke liye runtime me hota hai.
Isme wo sab info hoti hai jo current request ke execution ke liye zaruri hai:-
Current work item
Workflow case
Approval items
Attributes
Comments, notification template, state
Persistent Storage
Jo data permanent chahiye (jaise Request, ApprovalItem, WorkflowCase) wo database me save hota hai.
Matlab agar system crash ho jaye, ye runtime RequestContext khatam ho jayega,
lekin DB me stored Request aur approvalitems aur workflowcase safe rahenge.

Flow Example:-
Admin ya user request submit karta hai → Request object DB me save hota hai.
Workflow engine request execute karta hai → RequestContext runtime me create hota hai.
Approval, validation, comments processing → RequestContext ke through hota hai.
Execution complete → changes (approval status, comments, workflow state) DB me persist hoti hain.
RequestContext destroy ho jata hai (memory se clear).
--------------------------------------------------------
🔹 RequestContext Methods:-
-----------------------------------
getRequest()
setRequest(Request request)
getRequestDefinition()
setRequestDefinition(RequestDefinition requestDefinition)
getAttributes()
setAttributes(Attributes attributes)
getAttribute(String name)
setAttribute(String name, Object value)
getApprovalItems()
setApprovalItems(List<ApprovalItem> items)
addApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item)
removeApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item)
getValidationRules()
setValidationRules(List<ValidationRule> rules)
addValidationRule(ValidationRule rule)
removeValidationRule(ValidationRule rule)
getCurrentWorkItem()
setCurrentWorkItem(WorkItem workItem)
getWorkflowCase()
setWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase)
getState()
setState(String state)
getOwner()
setOwner(String owner)
getCreated()
setCreated(Date date)
getCompleted()
setCompleted(Date date)
getComments()
addComment(String comment)
getNotificationTemplate()
setNotificationTemplate(String template)
getApprovalMode()
setApprovalMode(String mode)
clone()
toMap()
fromMap(Map map)
toXml()
fromXml(String xml)
-----------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ getRequest() / setRequest(Request request):-
Purpose:-
getRequest() → Runtime me request object fetch karta hai.
setRequest(Request request) → RequestContext me specific Request object assign karta hai.

Example:-
Request req = new Request();
req.setId("REQ123");
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setRequest(req);
System.out.println(context.getRequest().getId());
Output:-
REQ123
--------------------------------------------------------
2️⃣ getRequestDefinition() / setRequestDefinition(RequestDefinition requestDefinition):-
Purpose:-
getRequestDefinition() → Request ke blueprint/template ko fetch karta hai.
setRequestDefinition() → Runtime context me specific template assign karta hai.

Example:-
RequestDefinition def = new RequestDefinition();
def.setName("AccessRequest");

RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setRequestDefinition(def);

System.out.println(context.getRequestDefinition().getName());
Output:-
AccessRequest
------------------------------------------------------------------
3️⃣ Attributes Methods:-
()getAttributes() / setAttributes(Attributes attributes):-
Poore attributes object ko fetch ya set karte hain.
()getAttribute(String name) / setAttribute(String name, Object value):-
Single key-value attribute ko fetch ya set karte hain.

Example:-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setAttribute("priority", "High");
System.out.println(context.getAttribute("priority"));
Output:-
High
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
4️⃣ Approval Items Methods:-
getApprovalItems() → Approval items list fetch
setApprovalItems(List<ApprovalItem> items) → Poore list set
addApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item) → Single approval add
removeApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item) → Single approval remove

Example:-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
ApprovalItem a1 = new ApprovalItem("Manager1");
context.addApprovalItem(a1);

System.out.println(context.getApprovalItems());
Output:-
[ApprovalItem{name=Manager1}]
------------------------------------------------------------------------
5️⃣ Validation Rules Methods:-
getValidationRules() → List of validation rules fetch
setValidationRules(List<ValidationRule> rules) → Poore list set
addValidationRule(ValidationRule rule) → Single rule add
removeValidationRule(ValidationRule rule) → Single rule remove

Example:-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
ValidationRule rule = new ValidationRule("Must have manager approval");
context.addValidationRule(rule);
System.out.println(context.getValidationRules());
Output:-
[ValidationRule{name='Must have manager approval'}]
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6️⃣ WorkItem & WorkflowCase Methods:-
getCurrentWorkItem() / setCurrentWorkItem(WorkItem workItem) → Current workflow step track karte hain
getWorkflowCase() / setWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase workflowCase) → Poore workflow case ko track karte hain

Example:-
WorkItem wi = new WorkItem();
wi.setId("WI123");

RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setCurrentWorkItem(wi);
System.out.println(context.getCurrentWorkItem().getId());
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
7️⃣ State & Owner Methods:-
getState() / setState(String state) → Current state of request (Pending, Approved, Rejected)
Ye method RequestContext me request ka owner set karta hai.
Owner matlab wo user ya manager jo request ko approve/reject karega.
Runtime me ye information system ko batati hai ki kaun se approver ke pass current work item hai.

getOwner() / setOwner(String owner) → Request ka owner jo request ko approve karega(usually approver)

Example:-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setState("Pending");
context.setOwner("Manager1");
System.out.println(context.getState() + " by " + context.getOwner());
Output:-
Pending by Manager1
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8️⃣ Created & Completed Dates:-
getCreated() / setCreated(Date date) → Request creation time
getCompleted() / setCompleted(Date date) → Request completion time
Example:-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setCreated(new Date());
System.out.println(context.getCreated());
Output:-
Thu Mar 23 10:45:00 IST 2026
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
9️⃣ Comments Methods:-
getComments() → List of comments fetch
addComment(String comment) → New comment add
Example:-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.addComment("Approved by manager");
System.out.println(context.getComments());
Output:-
[Approved by manager]
-----------------------------------------------------------------
🔟 Notification & Approval Mode:-
getNotificationTemplate() / setNotificationTemplate(String template) → Notification template manage
getApprovalMode() / setApprovalMode(String mode) → Approval mode (SEQUENTIAL / PARALLEL / NONE)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣1️⃣ Clone / Map / XML Methods:-
clone() → RequestContext ka deep copy
toMap() / fromMap(Map map) → Runtime object ko Map me convert / restore
toXml() / fromXml(String xml) → RequestContext ko XML me convert / restore
Example (Map):-
RequestContext context = new RequestContext();
context.setState("Pending");
Map<String,Object> map = context.toMap();
System.out.println(map);
Output:-
{state=Pending, attributes={}, approvalItems=[], comments=[]}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
